{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos400.erdos_400.parts.ii https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos400.erdos_400.parts.ii.","id":"vf_499998467ea96975","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #400: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. For any $k\\geq 2$ let $g_k(n)$ denote the maximum value of\\[(a_1+\\cdots+a_k)-n\\]where $a_1,\\ldots,a_k$ are integers such that $a_1!\\cdots a_k! \\mid n!$. Can one show that\\[\\sum_{n\\leq x}g_k(n) \\sim c_k x\\log x\\]for some constant $c_k$? Is it true that there is a constant $c_k$ such that for almost all $n<x$ we have\\[g_k(n)=c_k\\log x+o(\\log x)?\\] Current best: Erd\\H{o}s and Graham write that it is easy to show that $g_k(n) \\ll_k \\log n$ always, but the best possible constant is unknown. Prize: no. Tags: factorials, number theory.","id":"vf_b2da6a944f70ad72","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Candidate partial result.","id":"vf_f4be712b2bc417aa","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/400.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_499998467ea96975","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:400","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_499998467ea96975","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"vf_b2da6a944f70ad72","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf